<Layout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
    <div class="gif">
        <img width="300" height="259" alt="RaccoonSpaceGif" src="/space.webp"/>
    </div>
    <h1>Shaurya Srivastav</h1>
    <small>Computer Science and Engineering Student @ UC Davis 2026</small>
    <h2>About</h2>
    <p>
       Greetings! I'm Shaurya Srivastav, a UC Davis sophomore 
       pursuing dual majors in Computer Science and Electrical 
       Engineering. Beyond my academic pursuits, I have a flair 
       for culinary excellence, emphasizing minimal food wastage 
       ‚Äì a trait reminiscent of Sanji from One Piece. üè¥‚Äç‚ò†Ô∏è Outside 
       the kitchen, I'm deeply engaged in technology and artificial 
       intelligence.

        I'm currently involved in notable research projects at UC Davis:

        Project 1: Semantic Patent Search (Dec 2022 - Jul 2023)

        I optimized semantic patent search by implementing the MPNET 
        model, enhancing vector similarity calculations with Faiss. 
        This project also involved developing a patent search engine, 
        deploying it on AWS, and curating datasets through web crawling 
        and API integration.

        Project 2: Trojan and Backdoor Detection for NLP Models.

        My responsibilities here included generating poisoned data, 
        deploying models on a local "Rubi Chest" server, and running inference to 
        identify potential triggers for trojan attacks. Technologies used 
        encompass React, Hugging Face, Python, and more.

        Should you wish to delve further into my research or culinary 
        interests, please feel free to connect. These experiences reflect my academic prowess and diverse abilities.
    </p>

    <p>
    My broader skill set includes proficiency in full-stack development, encompassing front-end and back-end technologies, database management, security, and optimization.
